
# Commit Message (Conventional Commits)
#
# Format: <type>(<scope>)<!>: <subject>
#
# SUBJECT
#
#   - Use imperative, present tense: "add feature" not "added" or "adds"
#   - No initial capital, no trailing period
#   - Append "!" after the scope for breaking changes
#
# BODY (optional)
#
#   - Explain what changed and why, not how
#   - Contrast with the previous behavior where helpful
#   - Can include: testing notes, rollback plan, alternatives considered
#
# FOOTER (optional)
#
#   - BREAKING CHANGE: describe the impact and migration steps
#   - Closes #123, Refs #456
#   - Co-authored-by: Name <email>
#
# REVERTS
#
#   - Header: revert: <original commit subject>
#   - Body:   This reverts commit <hash>.
#
# TYPES
#
#   feat      A new feature
#   fix       A bug fix
#   refactor  A code change that is neither a fix nor a feature
#   perf      A performance improvement
#   test      Adding or updating tests
#   docs      Documentation changes only
#   style     Formatting or whitespace, no change to logic or meaning
#   build     Build system or external dependency changes
#   ci        CI configuration or scripts
#   chore     Maintenance tasks that do not affect src or tests
#   revert    An explicit revert of a previous commit
#
# SCOPE
#
#   A free-form label for the area that changed, e.g. api, cli, ui, auth, db
#   Omit if the change is truly global or does not fit a single area.
